{"article_id":"A7qxpWjvdrvRxkh6","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Special counsel Robert Mueller did not find","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that the Trump campaign \" conspired or coordinated \" with the Russian government","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to meddle in the 2016 elections ,","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"according to Attorney General William Barr ' s summary to Congress","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"delivered Sunday .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Barr ' s four-page letter outlines the \" principal conclusions \" of the nearly two-year special counsel probe ,","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"reiterating","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"that the Russian government sought to interfere in US politics","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"but that the investigation did not establish","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"that Trump associates aided them in their efforts .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"His summary also took up the other major element of Mueller ' s investigation :","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"whether President Donald Trump obstructed justice .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"Here , Barr cites language from Mueller ' s report ,","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"noting","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"that the special counsel ' s office did not draw a definite conclusion","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"as to whether the president committed a crime ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"but also that the report \" did not exonerate him . \"","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Barr adds","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"since Mueller did not make a determination ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"both he and Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein have ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"concluding","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that the evidence is not \" sufficient","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"to establish","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"the President committed an obstruction-of-justice offense . \"","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"The White House has seized on these conclusions as \" total exoneration \" -","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"\" No Collusion , No Obstruction , \"","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Trump tweeted .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"It may not quite be that ,","depth":4},{"id":29,"text":"though on the whole , Barr ' s summary is favorable to the president and his associates .","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"But Barr ' s preliminary summary letter is not the full Mueller report ,","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"which for now remains confidential .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"Barr ' s outline of the special counsel ' s findings doesn ' t elaborate on why or how investigators came to their conclusions","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"( or lack thereof ) .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Notably , it is also Barr ' s reading","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"- with the input of Rosenstein , and likely other DOJ officials -","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"of Mueller ' s conclusions , and , with few exceptions , not Mueller ' s own words .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"That ambiguity means Barr ' s letter leaves a few questions still unresolved .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"' s Andrew Prokop has an explainer","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"on what we learned from Barr ' s letter .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"But here ' s","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"we can ' t figure out from Barr ' s summary .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"1 ) How long is Mueller ' s report","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"- and how detailed is it ?","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Okay , this is kind of an obvious one","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"since Barr ' s letter is , by default , a summary of the report ' s \" principal conclusions . \"","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Barr ' s letter spans four pages ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"but the attorney general notes","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"that Mueller \" issued more than 2,800 subpoenas ,","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"executed nearly 500 search warrants ,","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"obtained more than 230 orders for communication records ,","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"issued almost 50 orders","depth":16},{"id":52,"text":"authorizing the use of pen registers ,","depth":16},{"id":53,"text":"made 13 requests to foreign governments for evidence ,","depth":16},{"id":54,"text":"and interviewed approximately 500 witnesses . \"","depth":16},{"id":55,"text":"That indicates a very comprehensive probe","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"that spanned continents .","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Some , maybe a lot , of that information might never be released","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"because it ' s classified for national security reasons","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"or relies on grand jury information .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"But how Mueller incorporated this evidence into a report ,","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"whether he explained","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"where these investigative threads led","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"and ended ,","depth":15},{"id":64,"text":"will certainly offer a fuller picture of exactly what Barr means","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"when he says","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"that Mueller did not find","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"that \" the Trump Campaign or anyone","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"associated with it","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"conspired or coordinated Russia in its efforts","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"to influence the 2016 presidential election . \"","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"Barr ' s summary says","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"the special counsel \" did not find","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"that the Trump campaign , or anything","depth":18},{"id":74,"text":"associated with it ,","depth":18},{"id":75,"text":"conspired or coordinated with the Russian government \" in its efforts","depth":18},{"id":76,"text":"to interfere in the 2016 campaign ,","depth":18},{"id":77,"text":"though it makes clear","depth":18},{"id":78,"text":"that Russia did meddle ,","depth":18},{"id":79,"text":"and points to Mueller ' s indictments against the Russian troll farm and Russian military intelligence hackers","depth":18},{"id":80,"text":"that targeted Democrats ' emails .","depth":18},{"id":81,"text":"( The special counsel defined coordination as \" an agreement","depth":18},{"id":82,"text":"- tacit or expressed -","depth":18},{"id":83,"text":"between the Trump campaign and the Russian government on election interference . \" )","depth":17},{"id":84,"text":"But Barr also says","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"Mueller did not establish coordination or conspiracy ,","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"\" despite multiple offers from Russian-affiliated individuals","depth":16},{"id":87,"text":"to assist the Trump campaign . \"","depth":16},{"id":88,"text":"The \" multiple offers \" from \" Russian-affiliated \" individuals certainly sounds a lot like the infamous June 2016 Trump Tower meeting .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"It appears that Mueller found","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"that this or other alleged contacts between Trump associates and Russian officials did not rise to the level of criminality ,","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"or at least did not meet the definition of \" coordination \"","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"as the special counsel defined it .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"But the question is certainly going to be why .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Barr notes","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"that Mueller examined possible obstruction of justice offenses ,","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"much \" of which has been the subject of public reporting . \"","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"So it ' s not clear if Mueller uncovered anything beyond of what was already known","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"from firing FBI Director James Comey","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"to harassing then-Attorney General Jeff Sessions","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"for recusing himself from the investigation .","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"But on the obstruction matter , Mueller didn ' t draw a definite conclusion \" one way or the other -","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"as to whether the examined conduct constituted obstruction , \"","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"Barr says in his summary .","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"Instead , for each of the relevant actions","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"investigated , the report sets out evidence on both sides of the question","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"and leaves unresolved what the Special Counsel views as \" difficult issues \" of law and fact","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"concerning whether the President ' s actions and intent could be viewed as obstruction .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"The Special Counsel ' s report states","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"\" while this report does not conclude","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"that the President committed a crime ,","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"it also does not exonerate him . \"","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"Mueller ' s decision","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"to note","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"that the \" report does not exonerate \" him","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"is pretty compelling ,","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"and is likely a tidbit","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"Democrats will seize upon .","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"Justice Department guidelines say","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"that a sitting president can ' t be indicted ,","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"and Mueller was likely to be bound by these regulations .","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"That means wrongdoing on the part of the president is inherently a political question , not a legal one","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"- and that might be why Mueller did not draw definitive answers on this question .","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"Or it might be that the situation truly is murky","depth":5},{"id":126,"text":"and Mueller could not prove conduct one way or another .","depth":5},{"id":127,"text":"4 ) How much of Barr ' s opinion guided the obstruction summary ?","depth":4},{"id":128,"text":"Barr , in his letter , says","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"that after much consultation , \" Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein and I have concluded","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"that the evidence","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"developed during the Special Counsel ' s investigation","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"is not sufficient","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"to establish","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"that the President committed an obstruction-of-justice offense . \"","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"Barr states","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"that Mueller ' s findings did not appear to establish beyond a reasonable doubt","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"that the president committed an obstruction of justice defense .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"Barr assesses those standards on three pillars ,","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"as ' s Dara Lind noted :","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"1 . There was \" obstructive conduct ;","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"2 . The conduct was related to a prosecution or investigation ;","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"3 . The conduct was \" done with corrupt intent . \"","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"Barr and Rosenstein apparently agreed","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"that Trump ' s actions didn ' t meet those standards , at least enough","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"to warrant obstruction of justice charges .","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"But they don ' t offer too many details","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"on how they arrived at this decision .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"The attorney general does note","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"since Mueller ' s evidence does not establish","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"that Trump was part of an underlying crime ,","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"the \" absence of such evidence bears upon the President ' s intent \"","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"when it comes to obstruction of justice","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"- which basically means","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"that","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"without collusion ,","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"there can be no obstruction .","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"Barr says","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"this is not determinative","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"- meaning it doesn ' t say","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"obstruction offenses can ' t happen -","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"but it clearly factored into their reasoning .","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"But beyond that , he doesn ' t explain their thought process in detail .","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"And","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"without Mueller ' s underlying findings ,","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"it ' s hard to gauge how strong and compelling Barr ' s \" no obstruction \" conclusion is .","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"No , but it ' s pretty good for the president and his associates","depth":8},{"id":168,"text":"- particularly on the \" collusion \" question .","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"Yet it also seems likely that Mueller ' s confidential report is a very carefully written document .","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"The rare segments","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"Barr quotes in his summary","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"use very precise language .","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"For example :","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"As the report states :","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"\" [ T ] he investigation did not establish","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"that members of the Trump Campaign conspired or coordinated with the Russian government in its election interference activities . \"","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"\" Did not establish \" doesn ' t eliminate the possibility","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"that evidence existed of coordination or cooperation","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"-","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"but it does indicate","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"there wasn ' t enough evidence","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"to bring prosecutions against certain individuals or a draw larger case .","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"The Justice Department typically doesn ' t release damaging information about people","depth":11},{"id":184,"text":"if they ' re not charged with any specific crimes ,","depth":11},{"id":185,"text":"or explain why a matter doesn ' t rise to criminal prosecution .","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"while it does happen ,","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"it ' s done rarely and often under extraordinary circumstances .","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"All of which means the public probably won ' t know the full spate of Mueller ' s findings","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"- which means some questions might never be answered fully .","depth":9},{"id":191,"text":"6 ) When , if ever , will the public see the full Mueller report ?","depth":7},{"id":192,"text":"Who knows ?","depth":7},{"id":193,"text":"Maybe never .","depth":6},{"id":194,"text":"Barr said","depth":9},{"id":195,"text":"his \" goal and intent is to release as much of the Special Counsel ' s report","depth":11},{"id":196,"text":"as I can","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"consistent with applicable law , regulations , and Departmental policies . \"","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"The applicable law , regulations , and departmental policies will be the tricky part .","depth":8},{"id":199,"text":"As mentioned above ,","depth":8},{"id":200,"text":"the DOJ doesn ' t typically release information about people","depth":9},{"id":201,"text":"who are not charged with crimes .","depth":9},{"id":202,"text":"Mueller also relied on confidential grand jury information ,","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"and Barr says","depth":9},{"id":204,"text":"he will need to work with Mueller","depth":10},{"id":205,"text":"to determine what information needs to be withheld .","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"Mueller also referred some cases to other federal prosecutors ,","depth":8},{"id":207,"text":"which means some of his evidence in the final report is used in ongoing investigations","depth":9},{"id":208,"text":"and can ' t be released to the public just yet .","depth":9},{"id":209,"text":"All of this will likely prevent a full , unedited report from being made public in the immediate future .","depth":5},{"id":210,"text":"But Democratic lawmakers are almost certain to battle to get as much of it released","depth":6},{"id":211,"text":"as possible .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":423,"left":305,"right":422,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":305,"left":239,"right":304,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":221,"right":238,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":216,"right":220,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":216,"left":214,"right":215,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":0,"right":213,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":213,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":5,"right":219,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":6,"right":218,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":218,"left":7,"right":217,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":217,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":238,"left":222,"right":237,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":222,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":226,"right":236,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":12,"right":225,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":225,"left":13,"right":224,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":224,"left":223,"right":16,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":223,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":233,"right":235,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":17,"right":232,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":